 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#333333>(3/7/02 10:25:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=169.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Play Nice Policy</span><hr size=1> Big differance between  quad kiting and afk experience (though am not a big fan of quad kiters, that's just greed pure and simple). Quad kiter is at his computer, playing their character, they are actually playing. The AFK'er is doing nothing, thier pet kills the mobs, they get the xp, they watch TV, go out to the movies, catch up on sleep, or whatever. This might not sound too bad except that barring the server or zone crashing, there's no incentive for this player to give someone else a crack at these mobs. It is unfair to dominate a spawn for extraordinary amounts of time. A quad kiter will eventually leave when they are tired, bored, need to eat, or whatever, and hence free of the mobs for someone else to have a turn with, the AFK'er only need do so if the servers go down (or lives in some backwards country with metered telephone/internet service).<br>
<br>
Kinelaria <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhoudlum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Houd Lum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(3/20/02 6:39:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=169.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AFK XPer's need to go to #@$*</span><hr size=1> Using VI's popular phrase &quot;risk vs reward&quot;.  No afk camp is completely safe.  If anything aggros on you, you die, if pet has a bad fight, you die, if someone trains you, you die, and very likely cannot be ressed.  Therefore it is not something for nothing.  I have done it, and I have died un-ressable deaths.  <br>
<br>
However, if the afk'er is taking &quot;most or all of the spawns&quot;, 33% is probably too much, 17% (2 of 12 bloodgills isn't), or is interfering with the normal play of the zone, then there is a problem<br>
<br>
But pets define the mage class.  To use the pet to the best of its abilities is fine.  I have had mobs pulled out from under me by quad kiters trailing 2 or 3 mobs.  Is that &quot;playing nice&quot;?  But the druid/wizzies figured out how to use their class abilities to do it, so more power to them.<br>
<br>
Besides is it so different than a bard sitting in a safe area playing an instrument all nite to increase skill?  Or a player pointing their nose up in the corner of a pond, ocean, etc and maxing swim skill?  What about creating a monk just to feign in SF to watch for RF spawn so he can get guild there first, when he isn't capable of contributing to the fight.  In all cases you are using a char abilities to gain skill or an advantage while not actively playing.<br>
<br>
If you are not interfering with other players abilities to play and enjoy the game, then it should be allowed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucasitadgato.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casitadgato</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(4/4/02 9:05:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=169.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://us.f1.yahoofs.com/users/fd03f6a9/bc/My+Documents/sigpicmagehand.gif?bcSDn48AiUkV8egK WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AFK XPer's need to go to #@$*</span><hr size=1> Not that I support this behavior but it is rediculous to say that it is unfair because AFK experiencers dominate a spawn.<br>
